#: ../../../release/1.16.6-notes.rst:5
msgid "NumPy 1.16.6 Release Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.6-notes.rst:7
msgid ""
"The NumPy 1.16.6 release fixes bugs reported against the 1.16.5 release, and "
"also backports several enhancements from master that seem appropriate for a "
"release series that is the last to support Python 2.7. The wheels on PyPI "
"are linked with OpenBLAS v0.3.7, which should fix errors on Skylake series "
"cpus."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.6-notes.rst:13
msgid ""
"Downstream developers building this release should use Cython >= 0.29.2 and, "
"if using OpenBLAS, OpenBLAS >= v0.3.7. The supported Python versions are 2.7 "
"and 3.5-3.7."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.6-notes.rst:18
msgid "Highlights"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.6-notes.rst:20
msgid ""
"The ``np.testing.utils`` functions have been updated from 1.19.0-dev0. This "
"improves the function documentation and error messages as well extending the "
"``assert_array_compare`` function to additional types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.6-notes.rst:26
msgid "New functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.6-notes.rst:29
msgid "Allow matmul (`@` operator) to work with object arrays."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.6-notes.rst:30
msgid ""
"This is an enhancement that was added in NumPy 1.17 and seems reasonable to "
"include in the LTS 1.16 release series."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.6-notes.rst:35
msgid "Compatibility notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.6-notes.rst:38
msgid "Fix regression in matmul (`@` operator) for boolean types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.6-notes.rst:39
msgid ""
"Booleans were being treated as integers rather than booleans, which was a "
"regression from previous behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.6-notes.rst:44
msgid "Improvements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.6-notes.rst:47
msgid "Array comparison assertions include maximum differences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.16.6-notes.rst:48
msgid ""
"Error messages from array comparison tests such as ``testing."
"assert_allclose`` now include \"max absolute difference\" and \"max relative "
"difference,\" in addition to the previous \"mismatch\" percentage.  This "
"information makes it easier to update absolute and relative error tolerances."
msgstr ""

